@page "/tree-grid/context-menu"

@using Syncfusion.Blazor.TreeGrid
@using Syncfusion.Blazor.Grids
@using Syncfusion.Blazor.Data
@using Syncfusion.Blazor
@*Hidden:Lines*@
@using TicketData
@inherits SampleBaseComponent;
@*End:Hidden*@

<SampleDescription>
    <p>This sample demonstrates the Tree Grid context menu, which exposes contextual actions such as editing, deleting, exporting, sorting, copying, paging, and column sizing through a right click menu on rows, headers, and the pager.</p>
</SampleDescription>
<ActionDescription>
    <p>The context menu is enabled by setting the <a aria-label="Navigate to the ContextMenuItems property reference for the Tree Grid component" target="_blank" href="https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/blazor/Syncfusion.Blazor.TreeGrid.SfTreeGrid-1.html#Syncfusion_Blazor_TreeGrid_SfTreeGrid_1_ContextMenuItems">ContextMenuItems</a> property to a collection of default or custom items. Items are displayed based on the clicked target (header, row, or pager).</p>
    <p>In this demo, a self-referential support tickets dataset is bound to the Tree Grid, and the context menu includes the following commands:</p>
        <p>
        <b>Content (Row):</b>
        <ul>
            <li>Edit - Edit the row</li>
            <li>Delete - Delete the row</li>
            <li>Save and Cancel - Appear after editing a row to confirm or discard changes</li>
            <li>Copy - Copy the row content</li>
            <li>Exporting (Pdf Export, Excel Export, Csv Export) - Export the Tree Grid data</li>
        </ul>

        <b>Header:</b>
        <ul>
            <li>Sort Ascending / Sort Descending - Sort the Tree Grid data</li>
            <li>AutoFit - Adjust the width of a specific column based on its maximum content</li>
            <li>AutoFitAll - Adjust the width of all columns based on their maximum content</li>
        </ul>
        <b>Pager:</b>
        <ul>
            <li>First Page, Previous Page, Next Page, Last Page - Navigate between pages</li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <p>More information about context menu in Tree Grid can be found in this <a aria-label="Navigate to the documentation for context menu in the Tree Grid component" target="_blank" href="https://blazor.syncfusion.com/documentation/treegrid/context-menu">documentation</a> section.</p>
</ActionDescription>

<div class="col-lg-12 control-section">
    <div class="content-wrapper">
        <div class="row">
            <SfTreeGrid AllowSorting="true" AllowPdfExport="true" AllowExcelExport="true" TValue="SupportTicketData" AllowPaging="true" IdMapping="TicketID" ParentIdMapping="ParentTicketID" Height="312" TreeColumnIndex="1" DataSource="@Tickets" ContextMenuItems="@(new List<object>() { "AutoFit", "AutoFitAll", "SortAscending", "SortDescending", "Copy", "Edit", "Delete", "Save", "Cancel", "PdfExport", "ExcelExport", "CsvExport", "FirstPage", "PrevPage", "LastPage", "NextPage" })">
                <TreeGridEditSettings AllowAdding="true" AllowEditing="true" AllowDeleting="true" Mode="Syncfusion.Blazor.TreeGrid.EditMode.Row"></TreeGridEditSettings>
                <TreeGridPageSettings PageSize="5"></TreeGridPageSettings>
                <TreeGridColumns>
                    <TreeGridColumn Field="TicketID" HeaderText="Ticket ID" Width="120" IsPrimaryKey="true" TextAlign="TextAlign.Right" ClipMode="ClipMode.EllipsisWithTooltip"></TreeGridColumn>
                    <TreeGridColumn Field="Title" HeaderText="Title" Width="220" ClipMode="ClipMode.EllipsisWithTooltip"></TreeGridColumn>
                    <TreeGridColumn Field="Category" HeaderText="Category" Width="140" ClipMode="ClipMode.EllipsisWithTooltip"></TreeGridColumn>
                    <TreeGridColumn Field="AssignedAgent" HeaderText="Agent" Width="150" ClipMode="ClipMode.EllipsisWithTooltip"></TreeGridColumn>
                    <TreeGridColumn Field="CustomerName" HeaderText="Customer" Width="160" ClipMode="ClipMode.EllipsisWithTooltip"></TreeGridColumn>
                    <TreeGridColumn Field="Priority" HeaderText="Priority" Width="120" ClipMode="ClipMode.EllipsisWithTooltip"></TreeGridColumn>
                    <TreeGridColumn Field="Status" HeaderText="Status" Width="120" ClipMode="ClipMode.EllipsisWithTooltip"></TreeGridColumn>
                    <TreeGridColumn Field="CreatedDate" HeaderText="Created Date" Format="d" Type=ColumnType.Date Width="140" TextAlign="TextAlign.Right" ClipMode="ClipMode.EllipsisWithTooltip"></TreeGridColumn>
                    <TreeGridColumn Field="DueDate" HeaderText="Due Date" Format="d" Type=ColumnType.Date Width="140" TextAlign="TextAlign.Right" ClipMode="ClipMode.EllipsisWithTooltip"></TreeGridColumn>
                </TreeGridColumns>
            </SfTreeGrid>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

@code{
    private List<SupportTicketData> Tickets { get; set; } = new();

    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        Tickets = SupportTicketData.GetSupportTickets();
    }
}
